I can easily create grids in TeX if you want it, of any pitch, with any kinds of row or column headers, different thicknesses of lines, all of that stuff. I can even make the NES PPU background plan form using TeX, and you could even write the entire document using TeX, or some "Literate NES" program.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4734">zzo38</a> — Tue Jul 12, 2011 2:58 pm</p><hr />
